post_cb({"34419603": {"CommentCount": "6", "ViewCount": "241", "PostTypeId": "1", "ClosedDate": "2015-12-22T16:01:30.550", "LastEditorUserId": "908939", "CreationDate": "2015-12-22T15:50:27.847", "LastActivityDate": "2015-12-22T15:58:04.187", "Title": "Why can't I declare templated type aliases inside of functions?", "AcceptedAnswerId": "34419745", "LastEditDate": "2015-12-22T15:58:04.187", "Id": "34419603", "Score": "3", "Body": "<p>Why can't I declare a templated type alias inside of a function?</p>\n<pre><code>#include &lt;vector&gt;\n\nint main(){\n\n    //type alias deceleration:\n    template &lt;typename T&gt;\n    using type = std::vector&lt;T&gt;;\n\n    //type instantiation:\n    type&lt;int&gt; t;\n\n}\n</code></pre>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_34419603_34419603_0\"><strong>error:</strong> a template declaration cannot appear at block scope  </p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Why are we forced to put these declarations outside of block scope?  </p>\n<pre><code>#include &lt;vector&gt;\n\n//type alias deceleration:\ntemplate &lt;typename T&gt;\nusing type = std::vector&lt;T&gt;;\n\nint main(){\n\n    //type instantiation:\n    type&lt;int&gt; t;\n}\n</code></pre>\n", "Tags": "<c++><templates><typedef><c++14><template-aliases>", "OwnerUserId": "908939", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "34419745": {"ParentId": "34419603", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>The standard says so.</p>\n<p>From the C++11 Standard (emphasis mine):</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_34419603_34419745_0\"><strong>14 Template</strong></p>\n<p id=\"so_34419603_34419745_1\"><strong>2 A template-declaration can appear only as a namespace scope or class scope declaration</strong>. In a function template declaration, the last component of the declarator-id shall not be a template-id. [ Note: That last component may be an identifier, an operator-function-id, a conversion-function-id, or a literal-operator-id. In a class template declaration, if the class name is a simple-template-id, the declaration declares a class template partial specialization (14.5.5). \u2014end note ]</p>\n</blockquote>\n", "OwnerUserId": "434551", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "34419745", "Score": "3", "CreationDate": "2015-12-22T15:57:48.913", "LastActivityDate": "2015-12-22T15:57:48.913"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_34419603_34419745_1": {"section_id": 49, "quality": 0.8717948717948718, "length": 34}, "so_34419603_34419603_0": {"section_id": 5903, "quality": 0.5714285714285714, "length": 4}}, "n3337": {"so_34419603_34419745_1": {"section_id": 44, "quality": 0.8717948717948718, "length": 34}, "so_34419603_34419603_0": {"section_id": 5675, "quality": 0.5714285714285714, "length": 4}}, "n4659": {"so_34419603_34419745_1": {"section_id": 50, "quality": 0.8717948717948718, "length": 34}, "so_34419603_34419603_0": {"section_id": 7385, "quality": 0.5714285714285714, "length": 4}}}});